solution: ```class Solution {
    public int smallestValue(int n) {
        while (true) {
            int sum = 0;
            int x = n;
            for (int p = 2; p * p <= x; p++) {
                while (x % p == 0) {
                    sum += p;
                    x /= p;
                }
            }
            if (x > 1) sum += x;
            if (sum == n) return n;
            n = sum;
        }
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly factorize n and replace it with the sum of its prime factors (counting multiplicity). The loop stops when the sum equals n, which is the fixed point and the smallest value. Factorization is done via trial division up to √n, yielding fast performance for the given constraint.

